<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<suppressions xmlns="https://jeremylong.github.io/DependencyCheck/dependency-suppression.1.3.xsd">

    <!--
        SUPPRESSION POLICY
        ==================
        Each suppression requires:
          1. A <notes> block with: the CVE, why it cannot be fixed, and the reviewer + review date.
          2. A <cve> tag (not <cvssBelow>) so we block the exact finding, not a score range.
          3. Annual review — add a calendar reminder when adding a new entry.

        DO NOT suppress a CVE simply because fixing it is inconvenient.
        Only suppress when the attack vector is demonstrably not reachable in this application.
    -->

    <!--
        CVE-2025-7962  |  angus-activation  |  CVSS 7.5  |  SUPPRESS
        ---------------------------------------------------------------
        angus-activation is a transitive dependency pulled by Spring Boot's
        Jakarta EE compliance layer. EnderChest does not declare or use any
        Jakarta Mail / JavaMail / activation-framework API. The CVE requires
        processing of attacker-controlled activation data-handler content,
        which requires the Jakarta Mail API to be on the call path.
        Since we have no mail functionality, this code path is never reached.

        Reviewers: Pedro Conceição
        Review date: 2026-05-14
        Next review: 2027-05-14
    -->
    <suppress>
        <notes>angus-activation CVE-2025-7962: transitive dep from Spring Boot Jakarta EE layer.
        EnderChest has no Jakarta Mail / email functionality; the vulnerable code path is unreachable.
        Reviewed 2026-05-14 by Pedro Conceição. Next review: 2027-05-14.</notes>
        <packageUrl regex="true">^pkg:maven/com\.sun\.activation/angus\-activation@.*$</packageUrl>
        <cve>CVE-2025-7962</cve>
    </suppress>

</suppressions>
